FBIS3-45405 "drchi012_e_94010" FBIS-CHI-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 Southeast Asia & Pacific Hong Kong XINHUA Head on Visit to Malaysia Meets Prime Minister OW1801160294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1456 GMT 18 Jan 94 OW1801160294 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Kuala Lumpur, January 18 (XINHUA) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamed met Zhou Nan, director of Hong Kong branch of XINHUA NEWS AGENCY at his office here today. Zhou is here on a visit at the invitation of the Malaysian Government. During a cordial conversation, both men expressed satisfaction over the development of friendly relations between China and Malaysia in recent years, with the hope that the friendly cooperation in all fields will be further strengthened to enhance common prosperity. Zhou expressed high appreciation for Malaysia's outstanding economic achievements and its peaceful non-aligned foreign policies. He reiterated the Chinese Government's positive attitude towards the Malaysian-proposed East Asia Economic Caucus (EAEC) aimed at promoting South-South cooperation. At the prime minister's request, Zhou briefed him on the current situation in Hong Kong and the policy of the Chinese Government towards the Hong Kong issue. The prime minister expressed his full understanding on it. Zhou today also met Ahmad Sarji Abdul Hamid, chief secretary to the Malaysian Government and Abdullah Fadzil Che Wan, deputy foreign minister of Malaysia.
